org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.plugin

Class AbstractObservableReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.keyple.util.Observable<T>
      • org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.plugin.AbstractObservableReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<SeReader>, ObservableReader, ProxyReader, SeReader, Configurable, Nameable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractLocalReader

    public abstract class AbstractObservableReader
extends Observable<T>
implements ObservableReader, ProxyReader
    Abstract definition of an observable reader.
    • High level logging and benchmarking of SeRequestSet and SeRequest transmission
    • Observability management
    • Name-based comparison of ProxyReader (required for SortedSet<ProxyReader>)
    • Plugin naming management

      • startObservation

        protected abstract void startObservation()
        Starts the monitoring of the reader activity (especially card insertion and removal)

        This abstract method has to be implemented by the class that handle the monitoring thread ( e.g. AbstractThreadedLocalReader).

        It will be called when a first observer is added (see addObserver).

      • stopObservation

        protected abstract void stopObservation()
        Ends the monitoring of the reader activity

        This abstract method has to be implemented by the class that handle the monitoring thread (e.g. AbstractThreadedLocalReader). It will be called when the observer is removed.

        It will be called when the last observer is removed (see removeObserver).

      • addObserver

        public final void addObserver(ObservableReader.ReaderObserver observer)
        Add a reader observer.

        The observer will receive all the events produced by this reader (card insertion, removal, etc.)

        The startObservation() is called when the first observer is added. (to start a monitoring thread for instance)

        Specified by:
        addObserver in interface ObservableReader
        Parameters:
        observer - the observer object

      • removeObserver

        public final void removeObserver(ObservableReader.ReaderObserver observer)
        Remove a reader observer.

        The observer will not receive any of the events produced by this reader.

        The stopObservation() is called when the last observer is removed. (to stop a monitoring thread for instance)

        Specified by:
        removeObserver in interface ObservableReader
        Parameters:
        observer - the observer object
